<h2>Regarding account creation:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        A driver can create both a driver account and a user account with the
        same email address.
    </li>
    <li>
        The driver must provide mandatory documents before account validation,
        including: ID, professional auto insurance, front and back of driver's
        license, front and back of VTC card, vehicle photo, vehicle registration
        certificate, and indicate the maximum number of passengers desired in
        their vehicle.
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Ride management:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        The driver can cancel a ride, but beyond a certain number of
        cancellations, they may face penalties.
    </li>
    <li>
        Rides are offered to drivers based on their location or if a passenger
        has selected them as a favorite.
    </li>
    <li>
        Drivers cannot see all available rides, only those assigned to them.
    </li>
    <li>
        During a shared ride, the driver can pick up additional passengers going
        in the same direction.
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Passenger features:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        Passengers can view details of drivers suggested by the application or
        their favorite drivers.
    </li>
    <li>
        A "feed" function will be implemented later to share information and
        highlight drivers.
    </li>
    <li>
        Passengers will be able to select a ride only with their contacts (app
        users).
    </li>
    <li>
        If a contact is not registered, it will be possible to invite them by
        SMS with a 10% discount on the first ride.
    </li>
    <li>Rides can be shared or paid for in various ways between passengers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Savings management:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        When a passenger saves money on a ride, the amount is added to their
        virtual wallet.
    </li>
    <li>This amount can be used for a future ride or refunded.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Reservations and shared rides:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Passengers will be able to book rides for future dates and times.</li>
    <li>These reservations can be offered to users in the same area.</li>
    <li>
        For shared rides, the application automatically suggests options to
        passengers based on their position and destination.
    </li>
</ul>
